{{Top|legends=Near-Human}}
[[File:DrydenVos-ToppsFinest2023.png|thumb|right|250px|The near-human crime lord [[Dryden Vos]]]]
'''Near-humans''' was a term used to refer to [[species]] that were physically similar to, but still distinct from baseline [[human]]s.

==Near-human species==
Examples of near-human species included: the [[Zabrak]]s,<ref name="Ultimate Factivity Collection: Star Wars">''[[Ultimate Factivity Collection: Star Wars]]''</ref> the [[Kiffar]], the [[Uugteen]],<ref name="Aftermath">[[Aftermath (novel)|''Aftermath'']]</ref> the [[Mirialan]]s,<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> the [[Umbaran]]s,<ref name="AotG">''[[Star Wars: Aliens of the Galaxy]]''</ref> the [[Koorivar]],<ref name="Trkn">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref> the [[Chiss]],<ref name="Thrawn">[[Thrawn (novel)|''Thrawn'']]</ref> the [[Kage]],<ref name="Kage DB">{{Databank|kage|Kage}}</ref> the [[Tholothian]]s,<ref name="Unlimited Power">''[[Unlimited Power]]''</ref> the [[Twi'lek]]s, the [[Togruta]], the [[Theelin]], the [[Miraluka]], and the [[Pantoran]]s.<ref name="Inferno Squad">''[[Battlefront II: Inferno Squad]]''</ref>

==Hybrids==
Certain near-human species, such as Twi'leks, Theelin, and Mirialan, were able to [[Reproduction|reproduce]] with humans, producing [[hybrid]] offspring.<ref name="Farewell">{{Rebels|Family Reunion &ndash; and Farewell}}</ref>

